{"word":"κιθαρῳδός","slug":"κιθαρῳδός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>ϰιϑαρῳδός, οῦ, ὁ</el></b> [<el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:κιθάρα\">κιθάρα</a>, ἀείδω</el> ‘sing’ (<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ cp.\">cp.</a> <el>ᾠδός</el> ‘singer’ and see <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ᾄδω\">ᾄδω</a></el>)] ‘one who sings and accompanies self on the kithara’, <b>lyre singer <a href='B:730 14:2'>Rv 14:2</a>; <a href='B:730 18:22'>18:22</a>.</b> (Cp. the role of medieval minstrels.) <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:κιθαρίζω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:Κιλικία\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}